betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Rocket Transporter Station is essential for sending and receiving cargo between celestial bodies.

Transport rockets, similar to resource modules or gas giant harvesters, automatically move various cargoes. To make the system work, you need at least one pair of linked platforms.

The platforms have compartments for outgoing and incoming items (blue and orange, respectively), and they can handle liquids with dedicated buffers.

To link platforms, Shift+Right-Click with the Rocket Transporter Connector on one platform to save it, then Right-Click on another platform. To open the linker interface, Right-Click on a platform with the connector: it will display information about the linked platforms' locations.

To designate one of these points as the receiving point, click the button at the beginning of the row.

To launch the transporter rocket, the station must be fueled with liquid oxygen and hydrogen.
